§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $A ⊂ 𝗥$ be open. ⦉

  ‖ A function $f: A → 𝗥$ is ❬smooth❭ if it has derivatives
    of any order. ⦉

  ‖ Since differentiability implies continuity, every derivative of
    a smooth function is continuous. ⦉
